divine prince Rama who after fourteen years in exile from the Kosala.";i:15;s:41:"Please read our disclosure for more info.";i:16;s:142:"Also known as Fierce pose or Utkatasana in Sanskrit Chair pose is a dynamic posture that fires up your body and builds strength and stability.";i:17;s:123:"The pose gets its name for its shape when you practice chair pose it feels as though you are sitting in an invisible chair.";i:18;s:105:"In Tadasana or Mountain pose firmly root into the ground finding equal weight on all corners of the feet.";i:19;s:76:"Inhale to bring the arms up overhead moving the upper arm-bones up and back.";i:20;s:63:"Turn the palms to face each other or place the palms in prayer.";i:21;s:54:"Exhale to bend the knees as though sitting in a chair.";i:22;s:72:"Utkaṭāsana Chair Pose is a standing asana in modern yoga as exercise.";i:23;s:52:"It was a low squatting asana in medieval hatha yoga.";i:24;s:120:"The name comes from the Sanskrit utkata meaning intense or powerful powerful proud and fierce and asana meaning posture.";i:25;s:93:"The Benefits of Utkatasana Chair Pose Chair Pose stretches spine hips and your chest muscles.";i:26;s:90:"Chair Yoga Pose strengthens the immune system and gives relieves back pain and joint pain.";i:27;s:66:"This asana gives the stomach organs a decent back rub Furthermore.";i:28;s:38:"Invigorates the stomach and the heart.";i:29;s:54:"The anatomy of chair pose utkatasana February 26 2016.";i:30;s:97:"BKS Iyengar introduced the world to the idea of using props to change the anatomy of a yoga pose.";i:31;s:115:"He had a deep understanding of which muscles tendons bones and vital organs were involved in every asana he taught.";i:32;s:39:"He spent decades studying why pain was.";i:33;s:23:"Steps To Do Utkatasana.";i:34;s:110:"To posit Utkatasana or chair first of all you should spread a yoga mat in a clean place and stand up straight.";i:35;s:68:"To perform this asana you can also stand in the posture of Tadasana.";i:36;s:60:"Keep both your feet close to each other and keep both hands.";i:37;s:68:"Slightly tuck the tail and draw the abdominals in toward your spine.";i:38;s:54:"Keep your head in a neutral position and gaze forward.";i:39;s:37:"Hold this pose for 5-10 slow breaths.";i:40;s:92:"Inhale and press through your feet to extend your legs and return to Tadasana Mountain pose.";i:41;s:132:"In Mountain pose with the feet together or hip width apart inhale the arms forward parallel to the floor with the palms facing down.";i:42;s:41:"Exhale and bend the knees squatting down.";i:43;s:80:"Reach the hips down and back as if you were going to sit on the edge of a chair.";i:44;s:102:"Utkatasana Chair Pose also know as Powerful Pose Fierce Pose or Awkward Pose from the Sanskrit utkata.";i:45;s:29:"Powerful or fierce and asana.";i:46;s:199:"Posture is a standing posture performed by bending at the knees sitting back in an imaginary chair and raising the arms while aiming to bring the thighs close to each other and parallel to the floor.";i:47;s:80:"The Chair Pose in yoga also helps in the stimulation of the heart and diaphragm.";i:48;s:105:"Performing this pose is actually quite easy unlike other poses that seem easy but end up being difficult.";i:49;s:129:"The Chair Pose not only helps with stamina but also helps you perform all the standing poses by improving strength and stability.";i:50;s:84:"Utkatasana yoga pose also helps in increasing strength balance as well as stability.";i:51;s:93:"This asana will strengthen muscles of the back so that you can be cured with the back strain.";i:52;s:49:"This pose requires sitting in an imaginary chair.";i:53;s:95:"Procedure to practice Utkatasana Pose Begin with the Standing position make your feet together.";i:54;s:145:"Some postures like the utkatasana chair pose yoga position may come naturally to you with minimal difficulty in terms of flexibility or strength.";i:55;s:73:"However even after years of exercise certain postures may seem difficult.";i:56;s:109:"While doing the chair pose yoga stand with your feet hip-width apart and ground into the earth with the legs.";i:57;s:80:"Utkatasana yoga steps chair pose with the sixth variation one-legged chair pose.";i:58;s:101:"We also do this variation by sitting on our feet and we have also called it as one-legged chair pose.";i:59;s:46:"In this method we practice sitting on one leg.";i:60;s:113:"Chair Pose or Utkatasana in Sanskrit is a standing yoga posture that tones the entire body particularly the legs.";i:61;s:174:"The Sanskrit name comes from the words utkata meaning powerful or fierce and asana meaning pose and make no mistake Chair Pose can be a fierce posture for your thigh muscles.";}}